featured_reviews.review_id:
Built by Marhoom Muhammed Engineer Sahib Vathiyayath and now maintained by his family,  it is one of the biggest masjids in Kerala.
Excellent facilities. Open from Fajr time. Closes by 10 pm. A very better choice for spiritual  enhancement and  ideal place for I'tikaaf.
Zuhar and Isha Jama'aths at fixed times through out the year. (1 pm and 8.30 pm)
Fajr jama'ath is held 40 minutes after Adhaan.

Formal Friday sermon (Jumu'a Khutba) is delivered in Arabic Language.  Admonition speech held before the khutba is in Malayalam.

Spacious haudh- Vuzookhana (pond for making ablution) with neat seats.
Ample parking space.
